<subSubSection box="[813,876,1014,1040]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="5.[812,1457,1014,1710]" box="[813,876,1014,1040]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">NOTE</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="612" type="synonymic_list">
<paragraph blockId="5.[812,1457,1014,1710]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">
The superfamily 
<taxonomicName authority="Muizon &amp; Ladevèze, 2022" authorityName="Muizon &amp; Ladevèze" authorityYear="2022" box="[992,1174,1045,1071]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" rank="superFamily" status="n. superfam." superFamily="Pucadelphyoidea">Pucadelphyoidea</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1179,1315,1045,1072]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" rank="superFamily">n. superfam.</taxonomicNameLabel>
includes two clades, the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Muizon" authorityYear="1998" box="[1016,1189,1077,1103]" class="Mammalia" family="Pucadelphyidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Pucadelphyidae</taxonomicName>
and an unnamed clade defined below. The 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Muizon" authorityYear="1998" box="[1036,1209,1109,1135]" class="Mammalia" family="Pucadelphyidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Pucadelphyidae</taxonomicName>
include the following genera: 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall &amp; Muizon, 1988" authorityName="Marshall &amp; Muizon" authorityYear="1988" box="[899,1326,1141,1167]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Pucadelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[899,1023,1141,1167]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">Pucadelphys</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MARSHALL L. G. &amp; MUIZON C. DE" box="[1032,1326,1141,1167]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" pagination="23 - 55" refId="ref22591" refString="MARSHALL L. G. &amp; MUIZON C. DE 1988. - The dawn of the age of mammals in South America. National Geographic Research 4 (1): 23 - 55." type="journal article" year="1988">Marshall &amp; Muizon, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall &amp; Muizon, 1988" authorityName="Marshall &amp; Muizon" authorityYear="1988" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Andinodelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">Andinodelphys</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MARSHALL L. G. &amp; MUIZON C. DE" box="[864,1156,1173,1199]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" pagination="23 - 55" refId="ref22591" refString="MARSHALL L. G. &amp; MUIZON C. DE 1988. - The dawn of the age of mammals in South America. National Geographic Research 4 (1): 23 - 55." type="journal article" year="1988">Marshall &amp; Muizon, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall &amp; Muizon, 1988" authorityName="Marshall &amp; Muizon" authorityYear="1988" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Mizquedelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1170,1323,1173,1199]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">Mizquedelphys</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MARSHALL L. G. &amp; MUIZON C. DE" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" pagination="23 - 55" refId="ref22591" refString="MARSHALL L. G. &amp; MUIZON C. DE 1988. - The dawn of the age of mammals in South America. National Geographic Research 4 (1): 23 - 55." type="journal article" year="1988">Marshall &amp; Muizon, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall &amp; Muizon, 1984" authorityName="Marshall &amp; Muizon" authorityYear="1984" box="[981,1433,1205,1231]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Itaboraidelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[981,1137,1205,1231]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">Itaboraidelphys</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MARSHALL L. G. &amp; MUIZON C. DE" box="[1144,1433,1205,1231]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" pagination="1297 - 1300" refId="ref22522" refString="MARSHALL L. G. &amp; MUIZON C. DE 1984. - Un nouveau Marsupial didelphide (Itaboraidelphys camposi nov. gen. nov. sp.) du Paleocene moyen (Itaboraien) de Sao Jose de Itaborai (Bresil). Comptes Rendus hebdomadaires des Seances de l'Academie des Sciences, Paris, ser. II, 299 (18): 1297 - 1300." type="journal article" year="1984">Marshall &amp; Muizon, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="612" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[812,1457,1014,1710]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">
The unnamed clade includes, in addition to 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall &amp; Muizon, 1988" authorityName="Marshall &amp; Muizon" authorityYear="1988" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Incadelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1332,1455,1237,1263]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">Incadelphys</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MARSHALL L. G. &amp; MUIZON C. DE" box="[813,1119,1268,1295]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" pagination="23 - 55" refId="ref22591" refString="MARSHALL L. G. &amp; MUIZON C. DE 1988. - The dawn of the age of mammals in South America. National Geographic Research 4 (1): 23 - 55." type="journal article" year="1988">Marshall &amp; Muizon, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
the following genera: 
<taxonomicName authority="Cifelli &amp; Johanson, 1994" authorityName="Cifelli &amp; Johanson" authorityYear="1994" class="Mammalia" family="Asiatheriidae" genus="Aenigmadelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">Aenigmadelphys</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="CIFELLI R. L. &amp; JOHANSON Z." box="[934,1228,1300,1327]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" pagination="292 - 295" refId="ref20372" refString="CIFELLI R. L. &amp; JOHANSON Z. 1994. - New mammal from the upper Cretaceous of Utah. Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology 14 (2): 292 - 295. https: // doi. org / 10.1073 / pnas. 90.20.9413" type="journal article" year="1994">Cifelli &amp; Johanson, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Paula Couto, 1962" authorityName=", Paula Couto" authorityYear="1962" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Marmosopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1246,1385,1301,1326]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">Marmosopsis</emphasis>
Paula Couto, 1962
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Muizon &amp; Cifelli, 2001" authorityName="Muizon &amp; Cifelli" authorityYear="2001" box="[1031,1414,1332,1358]" class="Mammalia" genus="Szalinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1031,1122,1332,1358]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">Szalinia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MUIZON C. DE &amp; CIFELLI R. L." box="[1132,1414,1332,1358]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" pagination="87 - 97" refId="ref22894" refString="MUIZON C. DE &amp; CIFELLI R. L. 2001. - A new basal &quot; didelphoid &quot; (Marsupialia, Mammalia) from the early Paleocene of Tiupampa (Bolivia). Journal of Vertebrate paleontology 21 (1): 87 - 97. https: // doi. org / brt 8 zq" type="journal article" year="2001">Muizon &amp; Cifelli, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. As discussed in the phylogeny section below, we favor the topology resulting from the analysis with implied weighting of characters, which retrieved the four genera in a clade. However, we are reluctant to formally name this clade because we consider that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall &amp; de Muizon" authorityYear="1988" box="[1182,1332,1492,1518]" class="Mammalia" family="Macropididae" genus="Jaskhadelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1182,1332,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">Jaskhadelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be included in the taxon list (which we did not) but with substantial new and more complete specimens than the single maxillary fragment with M2-M3 known so far. If 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall &amp; de Muizon" authorityYear="1988" box="[815,961,1619,1645]" class="Mammalia" family="Macropididae" genus="Jaskhadelphys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[815,961,1619,1645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="612">Jaskhadelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was to be included in this clade (what is so far highly uncertain), then the resulting clade should be the family 
<taxonomicName authority="(Muizon 1992)" baseAuthorityName="Muizon" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[936,1309,1683,1710]" class="Mammalia" family="Jaskhadelphyidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">
Jaskhadelphyidae (
<bibRefCitation author="MUIZON C. DE" box="[1145,1298,1683,1709]" pageId="5" pageNumber="612" pagination="575 - 624" refId="ref22721" refString="MUIZON C. DE 1992. - La fauna de mamiferos de Tiupampa (Paleoceno inferior, Formacion Santa Lucia), Bolivia, in SUAREZ RIGLOS M. (ed.), Fosiles y facies de Bolivia. Vol. I. Vertebrados. Revista Tecnica de Yacimientos Petroliferos y Fiscales de Bolivia 12 (3 - 4): 575 - 624." type="journal article" year="1992">Muizon 1992</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
